                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <desc>
                    The work is a service book involving readings for the leaders and people of the church. Abbreviations of their titles are rubricated (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ሕዝ</foreign>, people, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ክህ</foreign>, priest, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዲያ</foreign>, deacon)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <desc>
                    The book is held in the shipping package in which it came from Ethiopia: Return address: Lidya Melaku, C/O Melat Solomon P.O. Box 3948, Addis Ababa, Ethiopia.  Recipient: Kenneth Hobby, 65 Mohawk Dr, Searcy AR 72143, United States.  The book is wrapped in an Ethiopian Newspaper, photos of which were taken
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </additions>
